Tom Rini writes:
> On Thu, 24 Dec 1998, Murat Arslan wrote:
>> How can I "completely" switch to Unix98 pty's ?
> 
> Did you upgrade to glibc-2.0.9x (or 2.0.10x)?  Also, in order to completly
> switch to Unix98 ptys, you'll need to find or create patches for some
> programs.  (ie util-linux, screen, a few others I think).
I suppose you will want this:
http://www.cs.uml.edu/~acahalan/linux/procps-981104.tar.gz
It gives you wide tty output for ps, along with other nice features.
